article.headline: North Texas 85, South Alabama 77
article.story: DENTON, Texas (AP) -- Jerome Rogers scored 17 points, leading five players in double figures for North Texas, which beat South Alabama 85-77 on Saturday night. Leonard Hopkins scored 16 points, Calvin Watson and Michael DeGrate both scored 11, and Shawnson Johnson added 10 for North Texas (10-9, 5-2 Sun Belt). Johnson also grabbed nine rebounds for the Mean Green, who outrebounded South Alabama 45-34. Malerick Bedden led the Jaguars with 18 points. Chris Young scored 17 and Carlos Smith added 10 for South Alabama (9-10, 3-4). North Texas built a 46-29 halftime lead.
